I have a different perspective.  Despite racing's technical and
geographic complexity, there HAVE been telecasts that did a great
job.  It can be done; the problem is, it just isn't done
consistently.

I'm a man of contrary expectations;  because football and
basketball are easier to cover, I expect less from them, and I
expect the quality of the racing show to be better.  Racing IS
difficult to cover;  as with all things difficult, just go figure
out how to do it well.

I also don't buy the &quot;can't keep track of everything&quot; approach as
a reason to cover not much at all.  Figure out where the gaps are
and compensate.  If you can't cover a 2 mile track, split it into
quadrants.  If you can't cover the pits well, get more
(competent) reporters.  If one statistician can't keep up, get
two.  And pay for these by eliminating the Draft-Tracker,
superfluous hosts, excessive graphics, Hollywood Hotel, etc.

